Package: VectorizedColorFilter
Type: Package
Title: Convert an Image to Grayscale and Apply a Two-Color Filter with Cutoff
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Eyvind Liljegren
Maintainer: Eyvind Liljegren <eyvind.liljegren@gmail.com>
Description: Provides tools for processing images. The function 'filter_grayscale' 
             converts an image to grayscale by extracting RGB values as a numerical vector. 
             The function 'filter_twocolor' applies a cutoff level and maps the image to 
             two specified colors. Built on the 'magick' package for image manipulation.
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>=4.0)
Imports: magick
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
URL: https://github.com/eyvindj/VectorizedColorFilter
BugReports: https://github.com/eyvindj/VectorizedColorFilter/issues
